{
  "doc_id": "1248",
  "text": "Cariprazine, a drug under development for schizophrenia and bipolar disorder, is a dopamine D 3 and D 2 receptor (D 3 R and D 2 R, respectively) partial agonist with preferential binding to D 3 R [CITATION_1] . Dopaminergic activity has been associated with the regulation of locomotion, reward, emotion, and affect, while dysregulation of this system has been implicated in both bipolar disorder [CITATION_2] ) and schizophrenia [CITATION_3] .",
